casebody.data:
No. 10-681. United States, Petitioner v. Donahue Dewar and Sharon King. 562 U.S. 1254, 131 S. Ct. 1570,

179 L. Ed. 2d 471,

2011 U.S. LEXIS 1815, February 28, 2011.

Motion of respondents for leave to proceed in forma pau-peris granted. Petition for writ of certio-rari granted. Judgment vacated, and case remanded to the United States Court of Appeals for the Second Circuit for further consideration in light of Abbott v. United States, 562 U.S. 8, 131 S. Ct. 18, 178 L. Ed. 2d 348 (2010).

Justice Sotomayor and Justice Kagan took no part in the consideration or decision of these motions and this petition.

Same case below, 375 Fed. Appx. 90.
